|
:INFO
Drying vs Cooking Fresh
Fresh pasta can be cooked immediately after cutting, or dried on a rack for 30 minutes \
to firm it up before cooking. For storing, dry fully on a floured rack for several hours \
then freeze in nests on a parchment- lined tray before bagging. Cook from

:TASK
Shape-Specific Tips to Remember
[ ] Tagliatelle: roll to setting 5, cut 6 to 7mm wide
[ ] Pappardelle: roll to setting 6, cut 18 to 20mm wide
[ ] Fettuccine: roll to setting 5 to 6, cut 4 to 5mm wide
[ ] Ravioli: roll to setting 7, fill and seal edges with egg wash
[ ] Farfalle: cut into small rectangles, pinch the center firmly

:QUOTE
Pasta dough forgives almost every mistake. Over-kneaded, under-rested, \
cut uneven. It still works. The only real failure is not making it at all.
